Let us practice further with these translation schemas with respect to the following examples:

| $C$  =  "is cheerful"
| $F$  =  "is festive"
| $G$  =  "is a geography major"
| $L$  =  "is a law student"
| $R$  =  "is relaxed"
| $T$  =  "likes table-tennis"

<br>

